item.title: Man charged with Geelong murder
item.description: A man has been charged with murder following a shooting in a Geelong suburb earlier in July.

item.title: Man charged over South Melbourne death
item.description: A 24-year-old has been charged for the death of a man almost a month after a passer-by discovered the body in a South Melbourne street.

item.title: Creep preys on teenager in public toilet
item.description: A perverted man who reached inside a cubicle at a public toilet in the Hunter region and touched a teenage boy on the leg before peering over the top of the partition is on the run.

item.title: Fears your super could be in danger
item.description: Industry funds are calling on the government to release a retirement income report which could potentially change the amount of superannuation paid by employers to their workers.

item.title: ‘They treated me like a dog’: Police officers guilty
item.description: Three Victoria Police officers have been found guilty of assault after pulling a man to the ground, punching him, hitting him six times with a baton, spraying him in the face with capsicum spray at close range, and filming themselves spraying him with a garden hose.

item.title: Shares dip amid fears of China-US tensions
item.description: Australian stocks closed Friday lower as growing tension between China and the US caused markets to lose confidence.

item.title: Prisoners tested after infections at meat facility
item.description: Precautionary lockdown measures were taken at two Victorian prisons on Friday as Corrections Victoria assessed if inmates had any exposure to positive virus cases at a nearby meat-packing facility.

item.title: Tassie bans key states from travel bubble
item.description: Tasmania will open its border to South Australia, Western Australia and the Northern Territory in two weeks’ time.

item.title: Alleged tax fraud ringleader behind bars
item.description: The man alleged to be the ringleader of a $17 million tax fraud syndicate will spend the weekend in custody after he was denied bail in a Sydney court after being extradited from Queensland.

item.title: ‘Poorer off’: Labor slams scheme
item.description: Early access to superannuation is making Australians poorer, Opposition Leader Anthony Albanese says.
